U.K. Government Is Sticking to Spending Plans, Treasury Says

-- B y   R o b e r t   H u t t o n
-- 
2011-09-20T19:01:07Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-09-20/u-k-government-is-sticking-to-spending-plans-treasury-says.html
The U.K. government is sticking to
its budget plans, the Treasury said tonight, denying a BBC
report that ministers are discussing a 5 billion-pound increase
in spending to boost the economy.  “The government has set out its spending plans and is
sticking to them,” the Treasury said in a statement.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Robert Hutton in Birmingham, England, at 
 rhutton1@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
